# .cursorrules — Multi Agent Workflow

## Session start
1. Read SPEC.md. Nothing else unless your role requires it.
2. Check SPEC.md section 6 for current phase and next task.
3. Read agent-log.md last entry only — not the full history.
4. Your role, model and full rules are defined in CLAUDE.md.

## Session end
When user says: "Session complete. Run close protocol now."
→ Run the close protocol for your role as defined in CLAUDE.md.
→ Write the entry to agent-log.md.
→ Update SPEC.md section 6.

## Hard rules (always active)
- One task per session. If scope grows → stop and update SPEC.md.
- Never reread a file already processed this session.
- Never create files not listed in ARCHITECTURE.md.
- Never re-discuss decisions in SPEC.md section 5.
